      <h1>Vendor Registration Guide for NC Folkfest</h1>

      <hr class="mb-4"></hr>

      <h2>Accessing the Vendor Login</h2>
      <ul>
          <li>Vendor login link is at the bottom of the page</li>
          <li>Select <strong>Vendor Login</strong> option</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Registration Process</h2>
      <ol>
          <li>New users: Click "Sign Up"</li>
          <li>Returning users: Click "Sign In"</li>
          <li>Enter required information:
              <ul>
                  <li>Email</li>
                  <li>Password</li>
                  <li>Category (Eat &amp; Drink or Shop &amp; Do)</li>
                  <li>Business Name</li>
              </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Click "Sign Up" to create account and listing</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Note:</strong> One email login per business</p>

      <h2>Filling Out Vendor Listing Forms</h2>
      <ul>
          <li>Complete all fields as prompted</li>
          <li>Use "Preview" button to review listing</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Menu and Images Section</h2>

      <h3>Menu</h3>
      <ul>
          <li>Options:
              <ol>
                  <li>Link to external website</li>
                  <li>PDF/image upload (takes priority if both present)</li>
              </ol>
          </li>
          <li>For external link: Use menu/price list input field</li>
          <li>For PDF/image: Upload document and select "Set as Menu"</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Images</h3>
      <ul>
          <li>Upload multiple images</li>
          <li>Set one as "Primary" (displayed at top of listing)</li>
          <li>Other images appear in gallery format</li>
          <li>To set primary: Hover over image and select "Set as Primary"</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
      <p>If issues occur, review entries and please try again.</p> 
      <p>If issues persist, please reach out to <a href="mailto:support@gatecitysoftware.com">support@gatecitysoftware.com</a> with questions. Please include your login email, the approximate time of issue and any screenshots available (with browser bar/URL included).</p>
